"The Echo Chamber: A wearable device that subtly alters your sensory input – olfactory, tactile, auditory – to simulate the immediate *feeling* of a chosen negative consequence.  It’s like a tiny, personalized, ethically dubious disaster simulator. Imagine: a scent of burnt toast and regret, a phantom pressure on your chest mimicking the anxiety of a missed deadline, a whispered voice echoing your deepest fears. Controlled via biofeedback, it’s a training tool for resilience… or a terrifying indulgence. Powered by a miniature bio-reactor that converts stress hormones into a mild, safe hallucinatory effect (patent pending!)."